        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:13AM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 213 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rolla, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of Morton and
southwestern Stevens Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
